Officials say while stun grenades were used as the crowd was barricading a road, nobody has been arrested. CAPE TOWN - Police will continue to monitor an area in Mfuleni following an early morning protest. Officials say while stun grenades were used as the crowd was barricading a road, nobody has been arrested. The police's Andre Traut says: Police members of the public order policing used stun grenades to disperse a group of people who protested illegally in Wimbledon Road in Happy Valley this morning. The situation will be monitored. 